text.section:
The Department shall issue a certificate of registration to a provider if the Department determines that:
the information and documents submitted with the feasibility study and application for a preliminary certificate of registration are current and accurate or have been updated to make them accurate;
the required number of agreements has been executed and the corresponding deposits collected;
any other license or certificate required by other appropriate State units has been issued to the provider;
the provider has submitted all proposed advertisements, advertising campaigns, and other promotional materials for the program;
the form and substance of all advertisements, advertising campaigns, and other promotional materials submitted are not deceptive, misleading, or likely to mislead; and
the provider has submitted any other information that the Department required.
